# PROJECT IDENTITY
Client: Nicon Built (legal entity: Nicon Built Pty Ltd)
Industry: Heritage renovation & custom building — 7 services: Heritage Renovations and Restorations, Heritage Home Extensions, Kitchen Renovations, Bathroom Renovations, Home Renovations and Extensions, Trades and Maintenance, New Builds (kept on site, not the main focus)
Site purpose: Quote requests via contact form / phone, routed through GoHighLevel (GHL). This is a MIGRATION of an existing WordPress site (niconbuilt.com.au), not a new build.
Site feel: Direct, plain-spoken, confident — short sentences, no fluff, no hype. Confirmed from the approved copy itself.

# DESIGN — NON-NEGOTIABLES
Visual system only comes from Concept 1b ("The Showcase") — see docs/content-notes.md for the CSS variable block, typography, and layout rules. Content/IA comes from Nicon_Built_Copy_v7_Approved.md in /reference, NOT from Concept 1b's "12 trades" wireframe content.
Palette: use only CSS variables defined in docs/content-notes.md
Typography: Archivo (headings) + Barlow (body) + JetBrains Mono (labels/eyebrows) per docs/content-notes.md
Buttons: rounded, 8px border-radius
Images: WebP with fallback, explicit width/height on every image (prevents CLS), lazy-load below the fold, preload the homepage hero specifically (current mobile LCP is 17.4s on the old site — this is the single highest-priority performance fix)
Every image is currently a placeholder pending Nick's real photography — see content/image-manifest.md

# COPY RULES
Use verbatim copy from docs/copy/*.md — do not paraphrase or rewrite
Kitchen Renovations and Bathroom Renovations pages are now client-approved (confirmed by Sara) — build them the same as any other page, no special hold needed
Testimonials page publishes 8 reviews, not 9 — the Johnny Andrianakis review has been removed per Sara's decision. Schema aggregateRating still uses reviewCount 9 (the real live Google total) — see docs/seo.md
Never invent a specific dollar figure, project count, or credential beyond what's written in the approved copy
Never use the "12 everyday trades" framing from the old Concept 1b wireframe — that positioning has been superseded

# TECHNICAL STANDARDS (from the Technical Developer Brief)
Semantic HTML5 — one H1 per page, heading hierarchy enforced, never skip levels
Custom-coded — NOT WordPress, no page builders (this is a hand-coded Next.js build, which satisfies that requirement)
Schema: LocalBusiness (site-wide), FAQPage (every service page + homepage + FAQ page), BreadcrumbList (every non-home page) — see docs/seo.md for exact JSON-LD
Performance targets: PageSpeed 90+ mobile & desktop, LCP < 2.5s, FCP < 1.8s, CLS < 0.1, INP < 200ms, TTFB < 800ms
Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 AA minimum. 4.5:1 colour contrast on all text/button combos (the OLD site's "Learn More" button disappearing against the dark hero image is the specific failure being fixed — do not repeat it). ARIA landmarks on every page, ARIA labels on icon-only buttons, visible focus states, skip-to-content link, real <label> elements on every form field (placeholder text is not a substitute), minimum 16px body font, links distinguishable without relying on colour alone, prefers-reduced-motion respected
All forms POST to a GHL webhook — never mailto: links. Form submit redirects to /thank-you/ (noindex, nofollow, excluded from sitemap.xml)
robots.txt disallows /thank-you and points to the sitemap

# ASSET NAMING
[page]-[descriptor]-[number].webp — e.g. home-hero-bg.webp, about-nick-portrait.webp, kitchen-renovations-page-01.webp. Full list in content/image-manifest.md.

