# NEVER DO
Never publish 0407699454 anywhere — it's Nick's personal mobile, explicitly a placeholder in the source brief, to be replaced site-wide by the GHL lead-gen number
Never touch or modify the Microsoft 365 email DNS/MX records during the domain switch
Never implement redirects in JavaScript — .htaccess/nginx only, and never create redirect chains (A to B to C)
Never use placeholder copy — all copy must come from docs/copy/
Never deploy with unresolved placeholders ([CRM NUMBER], [LICENCE NUMBER] etc.)
Never add dependencies not listed in the approved tech stack
Never ship a page with alt="" on a non-decorative image
Never invent which blog posts survive or exact location-page copy beyond the 5 chosen suburbs (Brighton, Armadale, Malvern, Albert Park, Elwood) — write their copy following the same voice as the approved pages, but flag it as new drafting, not verbatim client copy
